<p class="article-lead">A five-day raw-material procurement period is one purchasing milestone, not the total perfume delivery time. It may apply to suitable regular materials after formula approval and availability confirmation.</p><p>Before purchasing, the fragrance reference, dosage and batch quantity must be fixed. Packaging components follow their own schedules; decorated bottles, printed cartons and custom caps can take much longer. Incoming checks, compounding, filling, assembly, inspection and dangerous-goods freight occur after materials are available.</p><h2>How buyers should use the estimate</h2><p>Ask which materials are covered, whether stock has been reserved and what could change availability. Put the five-day node inside the full project schedule rather than advertising it as a five-day manufacturing promise.</p>
